<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 29 at 6:48AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Periods of snow and poor visibility this morning...
Periods of snow will affect Central MT this morning from
Raynesford to Grass Range. Visibility will be reduced to less than
one mile at times in areas of falling snow.
Some roadways could be snow covered and slippery at times,
especially hill areas around Stanford and east of Lewistown.
Additionally, north winds gusting near 40 mph will also occur
along portions of Highway 191 from Eddies Corner to Judith Gap.</description>
